    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-13T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-13T09:00:00-05:00" n="372"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.PA/11–1345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HWA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-13T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >November 13, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 13—4:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3838. ReDeptel 2280, November 5, <persName>Benton</persName> to <persName
                        corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>, repeating cable from London of
                    October 31. Educational and Cultural Organization. I do not believe it advisable
                    to approach Foreign Office on this question. British did approach
                        <persName>Vyshinski</persName> again in letter dated November 2, to which
                    they have had as yet no reply, and I cannot believe (reEmbs 3439, October 3,
                    repeated London as 490 and 3507, October 10, repeated London as 513<note n="24"
                        xml:id="d372fn1">Neither printed.</note>) that anything we might say at this
                    date would have any effect on Soviet decision and may cause annoyance that here
                    again we would be needling them obviously at the request of the British.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept; repeated London as 575.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
